* Iron Raptor simply sighed as she heard Prowl verify her question as well 
as the look from Kluster, both seeming to reflect the fact that she might 
have not made the right decision.
But she knew the risks involved in all of this...but the only bot who would 
end up getting hurt if anything bad happened would be her.
And Peace was worth that risk, but one still didn't have to be stupid about 
it.
She would have protection...one couldn't afford NOT to have protection when 
dealing with Predacons.
But she was prepared for the worst, and would handle the situation if it 
ever came around to it.
Iron Raptor turned her attention towards Battera at the mention of 
collateral.*

" What? Collateral? I don't think so."

* She looked at Battera for a moment longer before standing and brushing 
herself off.*

" Maximals only take prisoners of war...not Peace Talks. You'll be coming 
with us."

* Iron Raptor then looked towards the projector that stood behind Prowl and 
Kluster, her blue optics reflecting her concern for her two missing 
Maximals. Her expressing taking on a zoned out quality.
She was worried about them, deeply worried.
For all she knew, they could be completely scrapped and on the verge of 
death. Something that she didn't want to think of...but was definetly 
possable.*

" But, I have some important things to worry about right now."

* She continued to stare off into thought for a few more moments, her tone 
indicating that perhaps it was in the wiser to let her get back down to 
buisness before she left.
There was a lot on her mind and she had to sort through it before she would 
allow herself to be lead to the Embassy, and a few precautions to be taken 
care of as well.*
